<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.93/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department has received the following telegram from the American
                            Legation at Peking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Request received from the Minister for Foreign Affairs that
                                    instructions be given our Minister in Ecuador to use his good
                                    offices for the protection of Chinese who have been attacked and
                                    have had no redress from the Government of Ecuador.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Guided by Department’s No. 61 of August 22, 1908,<note n="1" xml:id="d647fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1908#pg_61">For. Rel. 1908, pp. 61</ref>–<ref target="frus1908#pg_62">62</ref>.</note> you will, with the
                            consent of the Government of Ecuador, use your good offices for the
                            protection of Chinese subjects and their interests in Ecuador.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>